<dl id="n54147c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n54" href="#n54147c">N54 (VI.B.45)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n54all.htm#n54147c"> 147(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> child being born / native ungirdles <small>Orange</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="n54147c"><li>FW 25.20f </li><li><a href="../../flex/a/lexa.htm#n54147c">2010</a> </li><li><a href="../../flex/a/l39a.htm#n54147c">1939</a> </li><li><ms href="#n54147c">MS BL 47476b-474</ms> </li><li>JJA 50:278 <a name="ad8" href="../../ff/fdra/ada.htm#ad8">Usage</a> </li><li> <a href="../../flex/a/ad8.htm#n54147c">Draft: I.1&sect;1.8</a>/2.8</li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources">Pendant que <mark>sa femme est dans les douleurs de l&apos;enfantement</mark>, le Giliak exprime son inqui&eacute;tude d&apos;une fa&ccedil;on singuli&egrave;re. <mark>Il ouvre absolument tout ce qui peut s&apos;ouvrir</mark>. D&apos;abord sur sa propre personne; il d&eacute;fait les nattes de ses cheveux, les lacets de ses souliers, et ses manches. Puis il d&eacute;noue tout ce qui, &agrave; ce moment, peut se trouver nou&eacute; dans la maison ou dans son voisinage. t leur dur&eacute;e d&eacute;pendent du plus ou moins de soin qu&apos;il aura mis &agrave; ne rien laisser de serr&eacute;, nou&eacute; ou ferm&eacute;.&raquo; <br><font color="green">[While his wife is in labor pains, the Giliak expresses his concern in a singular way. He opens absolutely everything that can open. First on his own person; he undoes the braids of his hair, the laces of his shoes, and his sleeves. Then he unties everything that, at that moment, can be knotted in the house or in its vicinity.]</font> <small> Lucian L&eacute;vy-Bruhl, <a name="LBEM" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#LBEM"><cite title="source">L'exp&eacute;rience mystique</cite></a> (1938) 265</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
